Nsfas says it has already received more than 300,000 requests for funding for 2017. CAPE TOWN - The National Student Financial Aid Scheme (Nsfas) has agreed to extend the application process for funding for the coming academic year. This after several students missed the 30 November deadline.Nsfas says it has already received more than 200,000 requests for funding for 2017.Spokesperson Kagisho Mamabolo said: So between now and 8 January, we are assessing, evaluating and will be communicating with all those who have made applications for the financial aid. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)